{"body": "I'm not sure I agree with this change. To me, the namespace code is namespacing a url within a string literal, and never a parameter. For example\r\n\r\n    namespace \"api\" { }\r\n\r\nnamepaces things under /api\r\n\r\nScoping, on the other hand, can work with parameters and string literals, so when provided with a symbol, it's not completely obvious if it would be transformed to its equivalent string representation or if it would represent a parameter.\r\n\r\nFor example:\r\n\r\n    scope :api\r\n\r\nand\r\n\r\n    scope \":api\"\r\n\r\nwould do completely different things with this patch, which might confuse people.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/10216382", "created_at": "2012-11-09T05:58:23Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/8114#issuecomment-10216382", "updated_at": "2012-11-09T05:58:40Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 8114, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/luke-gru/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/luke-gru/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/luke-gru/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/luke-gru", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/luke-gru/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/luke-gru", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/luke-gru/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/349d851184514340f1757f3a71b6807a?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fa7e1d7d3049ac5512f00c12e92dae760.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/luke-gru/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/luke-gru/received_events", "gravatar_id": "349d851184514340f1757f3a71b6807a", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/luke-gru/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "luke-gru", "type": "User", "id": 500554, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/luke-gru/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523da89fbd354364b9008dae"}, "id": 10216382, "is